Since $\angle AHC$ and $\angle BHC$ are complementary to $\angle ABC$ and $\angle BAC,$ respectively, $\angle AHC = 180^\circ - 71^\circ - 46^\circ = 63^\circ$ and $\angle CHB = 180^\circ - 71^\circ - 46^\circ = 63^\circ.$  Therefore,
\[\angle AHB = 180^\circ - \angle AHC - \angle CHB = 180^\circ - 63^\circ - 63^\circ = \boxed{54^\circ}.\]

